text: Eugene S. "Gene" Fraise (May 7, 1932 â€“ November 27, 2020) was an American politician. He was a member of the Iowa Senate from the 46th district from 1986 until 2013. He was born in West Point, Iowa. Fraise was a member of the Democratic Party. Fraise died of COVID-19 on November 27, 2020, in West Burlington, Iowa at age 88. ==References== Category:1932 births Category:2020 deaths Category:State legislators of the United States Category:Politicians from Iowa Category:Democratic Party (United States) politicians Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic in the United States
